title: CMB volleyball can’t keep up with South Hamilton
text:
CMB volleyball can’t keep up with South Hamilton Published: Friday, Oct. 16, 2015 10:44 a.m. CDT By Troy Hyde Newton Daily News 
JEWELL — Collins-Maxwell/Baxter’s volleyball team stayed in neutral Thursday during a Heart of Iowa Conference match with South Hamilton. 
The Hawks got 18 kills from Ady Wintermote, 23 assists from Alissa Moss and 10 digs from Anna Moss during their 25-14, 25-18, 25-14 sweep of the Raiders on Senior Night. 
Statistics for CMB were not available at press time. It was the Raiders’ eighth straight loss. CMB is now 10-14 overall and 2-6 in HOIC play. South Hamilton improved to 17-8 overall and 6-2 in league matches. 
It was the regular season finale for the Raiders. They play in a Class 3A regional tourney opener at 7 p.m. on Oct. 26 at North Polk.
